AB  - We present case histories of four patients treated with
      artemether-lumefantrine for falciparum malaria in UK hospitals in 2015 to
      2016. Each subsequently presented with recurrent symptoms and Plasmodium
      falciparum parasitemia within 6 weeks of treatment with no intervening
      travel to countries where malaria is endemic. Parasite isolates, all of
      African origin, harbored variants at some candidate resistance loci. No
      evidence of pfk13-mediated artemisinin resistance was found. Vigilance for
      signs of unsatisfactory antimalarial efficacy among imported cases of
      malaria is recommended.
