AB  - We evaluated markers of sulfadoxine-pyrimethamine (SP) resistance in
      Plasmodium falciparum among 254 returned migrant workers in China from
      Africa from 2013 to 2016. High prevalences of pfdhfr (97.2%) and pfdhps
      (96.5%) mutations were observed. The partially resistant genotype was
      homogeneously distributed in Africa with a modestly high prevalence (48%),
      whereas the super resistant genotype was only found in West Africa with a
      very low frequency (1.2%). The findings provided baseline data about the
      molecular markers of SP resistance.
