AB  - Polymorphisms and the overexpression of transporter genes, especially of
      the ATP-binding cassette superfamily, have been involved in antimalarial
      drug resistance. The objective of this study was to use 77 Senegalese
      Plasmodium falciparum isolates to evaluate the association between the
      number of Asn residues in the polymorphic microsatellite region of the
      Plasmodium falciparum multidrug resistance 6 gene (Pfmdr6) and the ex vivo
      susceptibility to antimalarials. A significant association was observed
      between the presence of 7 or 9 Asn repeats and reduced susceptibility to
      quinine.
