AB  - Artemisinin-resistant Plasmodium falciparum has been identified by WHO in
      the Greater Mekong subregion. While there is no report on artemisinin
      resistance in Africa and South America by now, related surveillance
      measures have been taken place. The genes related artemisinin-resistance
      has been identified and the molecular markers will be used for large-scale
      surveillance efforts to contain artemisinin resistance. The emergence and
      spread of artemisinin resistance worldwide is a present danger and needs
      more attention. This article reviews the progress of artemisininresistance
      malaria parasites and artemisinin-based combination therapies.
