AB  - The rapid emergence of drug-resistant malaria parasites during the course
      of an infection remains a major challenge for providing accurate treatment
      guidelines. This is particularly important in cases of malaria treatment
      failure. Using a previously well-characterized case of malaria treatment
      failure, we show the utility of using next-generation sequencing for early
      detection of the rise and selection of a previously reported
      atovaquone-proguanil (malarone) drug resistance-associated mutation.
